BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic Republic of Iran calls for international 
cooperation for transfer of space technology to the developing 
countries. 
  Islamic Republic of Iran's representative mentioned the 
point 
in the 33rd session of the Legal Subcommittee for Peaceful Use 
of Outer Space saying the space technology should be put at the 
disposal of larger number of countries and people in the world. 
The Iranian representative said outer space should be allocated 
to peaceful activities based on the UN ratifications. The 
Iranian representative has mentioned the space technology as a 
helpful means for promotion of communication for protection of 
the living environment and predictions of natural incidents, 
calling on the UN to make efforts to attain the objective 
through creating regional mechanisms. 
  The Legal Subcommittee of Peaceful use of outer space 
includes 53 members with the Islamic Republic of Iran being one 
of them. 

